how to fix data skew[one partition has too much data]
1. salting - add random number to keys to distribute data evenly across partitions.
    from pyspark.sql.functions import col, rand
    df_large = df_large.withColumn("salt", (rand()*5).cast("int"))
    df_large = df_large.withColumn("new_key", col("country") + "_" + col("salt"))

        Before Salting (Skew)
        --------------------
        P0 → █████████████████
        P1 → ██
        P2 → █

        After Salting
        --------------------
        P0 → ███
        P1 → ████
        P2 → ███
        P3 → ████
        P4 → ███

2. broadcast join- if one table is small
3. repartition on join column
4. skew join hints - df.hint("skew") -- it tells the spark that This table has skewed data — please handle it intelligently

