                CACHE AND PERSIST
Both are used to store intermediate data in memory (or disk) so Spark doesn’t recompute it again and again.

CACHE - Stores data in RAM only 
        df.cache()
        If memory is not enough → recomputation happens

PERSIST - we can choice where to store data
        from pyspark import StorageLevel
        df.persist(StorageLevel.MEMORY_AND_DISK)

        🔹 Storage Levels (Important 🔥)
        Level	                Meaning
        MEMORY_ONLY	            Store only in RAM
        MEMORY_AND_DISK	        RAM + spill to disk if needed
        DISK_ONLY	            Store only on disk
        MEMORY_ONLY_SER	        Serialized (less memory)

